wikipedia_page.main: Admiral Sir Richard Edward Tracey  (24 January 1837 – 7 March 1907) was a Royal Navy officer who became President of the Royal Naval College, Greenwich.

response: The mission was led by Commander, later Admiral, Sir Richard Tracey, and composed of several officers and warrant officers.  Commander Tracey, who earlier in his career had served as a junior officer on HMS Euryalus, was a veteran of active operations at both the Bombardment of Kagoshima in August 1863 and the attack on Shimonoseki in September 1864.
Richard Tracey (1943–2020) is a British politician
